It's gatekeeping but with reason.

Right, because the torso is a cylinder in space. If you can draw that then drawing "a torso" is really how to convert the cylinder volume into a natural and organic form. tropes:
>waifur and mc are perfect functional human beings with no issues in their relationship. they also have no challenges to overcome.
there is only one story that i can think of that has done this well. the main problem with this trope is that there is no room for growth because the characters have already grown. why should i be attached to your character if i have not seen a single obstacle get in their way? atleast show me some interactions between the two that are fun or interesting. what is their goal in the story?
>mc and waifur are friends but for some odd reason they talk like acquaintances.
usually with friends you see people shooting the shit or talking about random mundane things. alot of the time they have inside jokes. they have chemistry and will play off eachother. some writers sadly forget this and just have the two characters just do nice things for eachother as a substitute.
>"i love you because i've always wanted a human boyfriend"
if the only reason your love interest is in love with your main character is because of his species then something is wrong with this relationship. that ain't love, it's lust.

for a story to work you need to have an idea and then expand on it. you need a set up in order for there to be a payoff. a lead up to a wedding is more stressful than just being at the altar at the start of a story. show, dont tell. you can name a character anon but for the love of god please make them a character and not a self insert.
